typewriters.


292
00:21:08,396 --> 00:21:10,926
He wanted a solution
for producing print


293
00:21:11,726 --> 00:21:13,636
that didn't require vision.


294
00:21:14,156 --> 00:21:18,036
That someone can do by touch.


295
00:21:18,036 --> 00:21:22,896
Now Turri had a lover who was
blind, and he wanted for her


296
00:21:22,896 --> 00:21:26,206
to be able to write
him love letters.


297
00:21:26,486 --> 00:21:29,416
So he designed the first, one
of the first working typewriters


298
00:21:29,416 --> 00:21:31,526
as a possible solution.


299
00:21:32,466 --> 00:21:37,166
And now today, around the world,
we have lots of touch typists,


